 with respect to aesthetic expressions and movements, often universalized in its meanings,  may require the use of the term \'93culturalist\'94 to refer to the rhetoric of groups \'93consciously in the making.\'94  Appadurai\rquote 
s proposal for a distinct use of \'93culturalist\'94 is logically intertwined with feminist cultural history\rquote s interest in \'93rhetorics\'94 as intertwined with \'93poetics.\'94}}}{\fs24 
